[Patient] What kind of exercises can I do with limited resources?
[Educator] You can try walking, bodyweight exercises, or online workout videos for free.
[Patient] I can't afford gym memberships or equipment, what should I do?
[Educator] Use household items for exercise, join community programs, or seek financial assistance for support.
[Patient] Is it safe for me to exercise with my heart condition?
[Educator] Start slow and gradually increase intensity, listen to your body, and stop if you feel unwell.
[Patient] How often should I exercise to manage my heart failure?
[Educator] Aim for at least 30 minutes of moderate exercise most days of the week.
[Patient] I don't feel motivated to exercise, what should I do?
[Educator] Find a workout buddy, set realistic goals, reward yourself, and remember the benefits of exercise.
[Patient] Can I exercise outdoors in my neighborhood?
[Educator] Yes, if it's safe, take advantage of outdoor spaces for walking or other activities.
[Patient] Are there any specific exercises I should avoid with heart failure?
[Educator] Avoid high-intensity activities, heavy lifting, and exercises that strain your heart too much.
[Patient] How can I stay consistent with exercise despite financial constraints?
[Educator] Look for free resources, get creative with household items, and prioritize your health for long-term benefits.
